112
00:15:46,998 --> 00:15:55,383
One of these responsibilities is acquiring the necessary rights and private and public lands for the design, construction, and implementation of this project.

113
00:15:56,282 --> 00:16:03,405
My function is to review and recommend procedures that the city of Medford and or DCR will use in acquiring these rights.

114
00:16:04,026 --> 00:16:08,148
The procedures used must comply with both federal and state regulations.

115
00:16:08,988 --> 00:16:14,591
Affected property owners' rights are protected under our Massachusetts general laws, primarily Chapter 79.

116
00:16:16,172 --> 00:16:23,975
And because this project is receiving federal funds, the property owners' rights are further defined under Title III of the Real Property Act of 1970 as amended.

117
00:16:26,806 --> 00:16:30,407
At this time, the only needed right-of-way parcels are owned by DCR.

118
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:36,969
DCR will be issuing permits, license, and other agreements as needed for the protection of the federal investment.

119
00:16:37,950 --> 00:16:45,212
As the design progresses, if other property owners are impacted by this project, they will be contacted by the City of Medford's municipal officials.

120
00:16:45,892 --> 00:16:52,855
They will present the proposed impacts to each owner and discuss the methods with which they may acquire the needed rights for the project.

121
00:16:53,735 --> 00:16:59,157
Frequently, municipalities will appeal for donations to minimize the acquisition costs for your community.

122
00:16:59,717 --> 00:17:06,600
However, donations are not required, and property owners are entitled to appraisal, review appraisal, and just compensation.

123
00:17:07,380 --> 00:17:14,443
